The students measure the surface tension of various concentrations of aqueous SDS (Sodium Dodecyl Sulphate) and use this information to study adsorption phenomena. The exercise requires about 2 hours of laboratory time, and approximately 4-8 hours for the data-analysis and preparation of a laboratory re- port.},
